The paper deals with the complexity of strings and their Kolmogorov complexity, which are topics closely related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of conditional complexity and prefix-free complexity also suggests information theory (cs.IT) as a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of games and the use of bounds, which are common techniques in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The study of Kolmogorov complexity also has applications in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of sets and their properties, which is a topic in logic and foundations of mathematics (cs.LO).
